gw.api.bean.compare.ui

Class EntityDiffDisplay<T extends KeyableBean>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.bean.compare.ui.EntityDiffDisplay<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DiffDisplay, HierarchicalDiff<DiffDisplay>

    public class EntityDiffDisplay<T extends KeyableBean>
extends java.lang.Object
implements DiffDisplay, HierarchicalDiff<DiffDisplay>
    Superclass for displaying entity diffs in a comparison UI (policy refresh in CC, pending updates in CM). This class can be used as is or subclassed by customers to give control over the UI or to add errors and warnings. If customers do not specify any particular EntityDiff type for an entity type then this is the type that will be used by default.

      • getLabel

        public java.lang.String getLabel()
        Label for rows displaying entities in the entity comparison UI. The default implementation returns a string of the form entityTypeName:entityName (for example Policy:123-456). The entity type name is the display name of the entity type of the EntityDiff, which can be localized by adding a display key of the form entity.TypeName (for example entity.Policy). The entity name is constructed by calling getEntityName(entity.KeyableBean) on either the old value of the entity or, if that is null (as in an add), on the new value of the entity.

        Subclasses can choose to either override this implementation entirely or to override getEntityName(entity.KeyableBean) to affect just the entityName part of the label.

        Specified by:
        getLabel in interface DiffDisplay
        Returns:
        a string label, must never be null

      • getEntityName

        protected java.lang.String getEntityName(T bean)
        Helper method to get the name for either the Source bean or the Compare bean to display in the entity comparison UI. The default implementation just calls bean.DisplayName but subclasses should override this method as needed to customize the way the entity appears in the comparison UI. Note that this method is called by the default implementation of getLabel(); if that default implementation is completely overridden this method will no longer be called.
        Parameters:
        bean - - either the Source or Compare bean for which we need a name
        Returns:
        String - the name to use for this bean in the comparison UI
